args:
When the royal army begins ruining forests and
lakes, Ilia intercepts their communications to
learn their ultimate goal. Upon discovering that
they plan to lure dragons to the capital and
destroy it—along with all the citizens—the
group rushes off to save the city.
No, sir. It appears she has not returned to\nher apartment in the slums, but we have\nyet to determine her actual whereabouts.
And what of the other woman?

It's highly possible they are together.
Still, we will make no progress searching
for them blindly; we must now proceed to
the next step of our plan.
We must force Ilia out of hiding,\nand I have just the way to do it...
The mana is terribly disturbed; we will be\nin dire straits if this continues.
First they burned Zeller Forest,\nthen they contaminated Lake Yuki.
They're systematically destroying nature,\nwhich means dragons are going to rage.
That seems both incendiary and dangerous.\nDo they think their actions will weaken\nthe dragons somehow?
I don't know, but I've got a VERY bad\nfeeling about all this. Better look into it.
Oh, I've got a secret tool up my sleeve.\nIt'll need some maintenance, though—\ncare to lend a hand, Mordecai?
You mustn't do anything dangerous, Ilia!\n...Ugh. She isn't even listening to me.
(Whatever is the kingdom planning?\nI hope it doesn't turn into something\nmore serious, but...)
Ta-daaaah! Behold my new invention:\na communication interception system!
This baby lets us listen in when people\nare speaking to one another, which means\nwe can eavesdrop on the royal army.
It sounds terribly risky. Are you certain the\narmy won't know you are listening in?
Yep! But if you're STILL worried,\nI'm happy to give a very long and boring\nrundown on exactly how it works.
*sigh* You know I would never understand\nit even if you did, so I will simply have to\ntrust that you are taking all precautions.
Thanks, Mom. Okay, switching it on now!
Our date was amazing... Oh, I just love\nyou so much, honey-pants!
Whoops! That's just a couple of lovestruck\nroyals gabbing away. Maybe I can retune\nthe thing a little...?
...oes well. There was interference from\nthe dragons, but within expected ranges.

This ought to be enough provocation.
Now then, what of progress on the other
matter? Has it not aroused suspicion
amongst the citizenry?
That's definitely Augus talking—probably\nto one of his flunkies.
Not a one, sir. All one hundred have been\ninstalled throughout the city; we now have\nbut to wait for the day.
Okay, WHAT are they on about?
Good. Soon, the dragons will succumb\nto their anger and attack the city.
Once that happens, the mana bombs\nwe set will explode and end them all.
Good work. Let us hope the day of\nour victory comes swiftly.
They've started destroying the forest and\nlake in order to provoke the dragons.
And when they invade the city, the mana\nbombs will turn it into a sea of fire.
AND they're not informing the citizens\nbecause they don't want the dragons\nto notice anything unusual!
These people are just the WORST!
So what will we do, Ilia?
Well, the smart thing is probably to run\nsomewhere far away and wait for all this\nto play out however it does...
But doing that would make us a bunch of\nselfish trash no better than Augus.
There are MILLIONS of people in the city,\nand I won't stand by and watch them burn.
I have to stop this—no matter what.\nWill you come with me?
Ilia, no! You can't just run into such danger\nwithout so much as a plan!
I DO have a plan: I'm gonna disarm the\nbombs by nullifying the mana inside 'em.
It should be easy enough to suss out the\nlocations of the mana bombs if I look\nat a map and the city's layout.
Because they'll be set in locations that\nwill be effective for taking down the\nattacking dragons.
Can the four of us really disarm\none hundred bombs?
I don't know—but we have to try.
I understand what you're saying, but...
Lemme guess: You're worried about me?
Though it is a horrible thing to say,\nyour life is more precious to me than\nthe lives of a million strangers.
Yeah, Mordecai. It is. But it's precisely\nBECAUSE Meene loved me and raised me\nthat I know this:
All those inhabitants of the capital also\nhave people they love.
The pain of losing so much is just...\nit's unimaginable. So I don't have a\nchoice here—I have to act.
I'm sorry. I don't know what got into me.\nYou are correct, of course.
Besides, it just means I will have to\ngo with you and ensure you remain safe.
Thanks, guys. In that case, we'll sneak into\nthe capital at night and get to disarming.\nEverybody good with that?
If we head out now, things should be\npretty quiet once we arrive.
But we are some distance from the city!\nIf we leave now, we'll reach the capital\njust as the sun is beginning to rise!
Sure, if we go on foot.
Sister, you have NO idea. Hee hee!\nStep right this way...
